{"type":"text","timestamp":1775844611060,"sessionID":"ses_2876ac4d8ffepOkZtbvcnOOJQB","part":{"id":"prt_d78962998001rQxrxpFdcFm32b","messageID":"msg_d78960468001umIEJll5JpQ0n6","sessionID":"ses_2876ac4d8ffepOkZtbvcnOOJQB","type":"text","text":"## AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Implementation Summary\n\n### What Was Completed\n\n**Core Functionality (Tasks 1-12):**\n- ✅ **SandboxController**: Full lifecycle management with CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox, CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox, GetSession, DeleteSession\n- ✅ **K8sClient**: Complete Kubernetes integration for Sandbox operations (GetAgentRuntime, GetCodeInterpreter, CreateSandbox, DeleteSandbox, GetPodIP, GetSecret, WatchPods)\n- ✅ **Sandbox CR builders**: buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR and buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR with proper labels, annotations, and lifecycle management\n- ✅ **EntryPoint builder**: buildEntryPoints for constructing API entry points from pod IPs and ports\n- ✅ **Utility functions**: RandString, generateSandboxName, convertEntryPoints, convertToAPIEntryPoints\n\n**API & Types (Tasks 3-4, 14):**\n- ✅ **API types**: CreateSandboxRequest/Response, GetSessionRequest/Response, DeleteSessionRequest/Response, EntryPoint\n- ✅ **Internal types**: SandboxInfo, SandboxEntryPoint, validation logic with error constants\n- ✅ **Request validation**: ValidateCreateSandboxRequest with proper error handling\n\n**HTTP Layer (Tasks 13, 15-16):**\n- ✅ **HTTP handlers**: CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox, CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox, GetSession, DeleteSession, Health\n- ✅ **Server setup**: Complete HTTP server with Gin framework, route registration for `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter`, `/v1/sessions/:sessionId`, `/health`\n- ✅ **Middleware**: Recovery, Logging, CORS middleware implemented\n- ✅ **Response formatting**: api.JSON and api.Error helpers for consistent responses\n\n**Session Management (Task 17):**\n- ✅ **8-hour session expiration**: Default expiration time with ExpiresAt field\n- ✅ **Last activity tracking**: LastActivityAt timestamp\n- ✅ **Garbage collector**: Automated cleanup of expired and inactive sessions (beyond original scope)\n\n**Storage & Configuration:**\n- ✅ **Redis/Valkey integration**: Store interface for session persistence\n- ✅ **Configuration**: Server, Redis, K8s, Session configuration structs\n- ✅ **K8s auth**: K8sAuthenticator for Kubernetes token authentication\n\n**Tests:**\n- ✅ **Unit tests**: Basic test coverage in controller_test.go, handler_test.go, api/response_test.go, config_test.go, middleware_test.go, client/k8s_client_test.go\n\n### What Was Deferred\n\n**Comprehensive Testing (Task 18):**\n- ❌ **Full integration tests**: Missing end-to-end tests for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter sandbox creation\n- ❌ **Error scenario tests**: Limited testing for timeout, partial failures, non-existent workloads\n- ❌ **Concurrent tests**: No tests for concurrent sandbox creation\n- ❌ **Higher test coverage**: Need >80% code coverage as specified in success criteria\n\n**Documentation (Task 19):**\n- ❌ **Package READMEs**: No pkg/workloadmanager/controller/README.md, pkg/workloadmanager/handler/README.md\n- ❌ **Main README**: No pkg/workloadmanager/README.md with architecture diagram and setup instructions\n- ❌ **Inline documentation**: Limited godoc comments on exported types and functions\n- ❌ **API documentation**: No Swagger/OpenAPI spec\n\n**Final Verification (Task 20):**\n- ❌ **Static analysis**: go vet and golangci-lint not run/fixed\n- ❌ **Formatting**: gofmt not verified\n- ❌ **CHANGELOG**: No CHANGELOG entry created\n- ❌ **Main README**: Not updated with AR-005 information\n- ❌ **Release tagging**: Not tagged\n\n**Minor Features:**\n- ❌ **JWT token signing**: Not implemented (designed in spec)\n- ❌ **RBAC enforcement**: Not implemented (designed in spec)\n- ❌ **Prometheus metrics**: Not implemented (designed in spec)\n\n### Summary\n\nAR-005 achieved **core functionality completion** with working sandbox creation, session management, and HTTP API. The implementation includes garbage collection and basic tests. However, **comprehensive testing, documentation, and final verification steps** remain incomplete, which are essential for production readiness and maintainability.","time":{"start":1775844611058,"end":1775844611058}}}
